gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 106, Celtics 103
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Celtics, 106-103. Joel Embiid recorded 27 points (10-20 FG), 10 rebounds, four assists and four blocks for the 76ers, while Tyrese Maxey added 25 points, nine rebounds and five assists in the victory. Kristaps Porzingis tallied a game-high 29 points, along with six rebounds and three assists for the Celtics in the losing effort. The 76ers improve to 6-1 on the season, while the Celtics fall to 5-2.
